    "causal_summary": "OpenLTM-derived continuity phase — the **highest architectural fit** of the OpenLTM study. OpenLTM's \"document-ish\" surfaces (its bounded startup context block, its PreCompact markdown snapshot, its goal/decision/progress/gotcha facets) map naturally onto our markdown-native continuity ladder (`handover.md`, `implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity` frontmatter, spec-folder docs). The critical reshaping from research phase 010: OpenLTM's snapshot is a DB-derived projection (\"never the source of truth; the DB is\"); ours must instead **refresh the authored continuity docs**, which already are the source of truth.",
